>> time required: 45 minutes
>> image: https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/recipe-image-legacy-id-488691_11-ca2ba1d.jpg?resize=768,574

Heat the @oil{2%tbsp} in @a{} large pan and cook the @onion{1} and @garlic{2%clove} over a medium heat for ~{3-4%minutes} until softened, stirring occasionally. Tip in the @potatoes{700%g}, carrots and parsnips, turn up the heat and cook for ~{6-7%minutes}, stirring, until the vegetables are golden.

Stir in the @curry paste or powder{2%tbsp}, pour in the @stock{1.375%pint} and then bring to the boil. Reduce the heat, add the @lentils{100%g}, cover and simmer for ~{15-20%minutes} until the lentils and vegetables are tender and the sauce has thickened.

Stir in most of the coriander, season and heat for a minute or so.Top with @yogurt and{} the rest of the coriander. Serve with naan bread.
